</figureCitation>
); meso-anterior incision of tergite IX deep (
<figureCitation id="135E2A4CFF8BED5F2A27FF23FE27FF27" box="[296,415,152,178]" captionStart="FIGURES 88 – 92" captionStartId="28.[151,269,1752,1776]" captionTargetBox="[182,1404,194,1727]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[182,1404,194,1728]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURES 88 – 92. Chrysopilus caligatus sp. n., male holotype: 88 — Terminalia, dorsal view, 89 — Terminalia, dorsal view, female paratype: 90 — Terminalia, ventral view, 91 — Sternite VIII, ventral view, 92 — Genital fork (S IX)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177251/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Figure 
<number id="3DAD24EEFF8BED5F2A71FF23FE27FF27" box="[382,415,152,178]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="89.0">89</number>
</figureCitation>
); cercus brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDA36C9FF8BED5F2BCAFF04FE65FEEF" blockId="29.[151,1437,152,498]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis id="B911EADBFF8BED5F2BCAFF04FE9FFF4C" bold="true" box="[197,295,191,217]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Female.</emphasis>
Body length, 9.0–10.0 mm. Wing length, 6.0– 
<quantity id="4C9D9B2CFF8BED5F286BFF7BFC7CFF4F" box="[868,964,192,218]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" unit="mm" value="6.5">6.5 mm</quantity>
. Thorax and abdomen similar to male. Anterior margin of sternite VIII rounded, hypogynial valves with at least six long setae (
<figureCitation id="135E2A4CFF8BED5F2FB3FF53FA8CFE97" box="[1212,1332,232,258]" captionStart="FIGURES 88 – 92" captionStartId="28.[151,269,1752,1776]" captionTargetBox="[182,1404,194,1727]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[182,1404,194,1728]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURES 88 – 92. Chrysopilus caligatus sp. n., male holotype: 88 — Terminalia, dorsal view, 89 — Terminalia, dorsal view, female paratype: 90 — Terminalia, ventral view, 91 — Sternite VIII, ventral view, 92 — Genital fork (S IX)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177251/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Figure 
<number id="3DAD24EEFF8BED5F2E1BFF53FA8CFE97" box="[1300,1332,232,258]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="91.0">91</number>
</figureCitation>
); genital fork with anterior end strongly acuminate, distal apodemes wide (
<figureCitation id="135E2A4CFF8BED5F28BEFEABFB93FEBF" box="[945,1067,272,298]" captionStart="FIGURES 88 – 92" captionStartId="28.[151,269,1752,1776]" captionTargetBox="[182,1404,194,1727]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[182,1404,194,1728]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURES 88 – 92. Chrysopilus caligatus sp. n., male holotype: 88 — Terminalia, dorsal view, 89 — Terminalia, dorsal view, female paratype: 90 — Terminalia, ventral view, 91 — Sternite VIII, ventral view, 92 — Genital fork (S IX)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177251/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Figure 
<number id="3DAD24EEFF8BED5F2F05FEABFB93FEBF" box="[1034,1067,272,298]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="92.0">92</number>
</figureCitation>
); cercus two-segmented, distal segment elongated (
<figureCitation id="135E2A4CFF8BED5F2A87FE83FDBAFEC7" box="[392,514,312,338]" captionStart="FIGURES 88 – 92" captionStartId="28.[151,269,1752,1776]" captionTargetBox="[182,1404,194,1727]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[182,1404,194,1728]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURES 88 – 92. Chrysopilus caligatus sp. n., male holotype: 88 — Terminalia, dorsal view, 89 — Terminalia, dorsal view, female paratype: 90 — Terminalia, ventral view, 91 — Sternite VIII, ventral view, 92 — Genital fork (S IX)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177251/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Figure 
<number id="3DAD24EEFF8BED5F2AEEFE83FDBAFEC7" box="[481,514,312,338]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="90.0">90</number>
</figureCitation>
); common spermathecal ducts short, spermathecal ducts long; spermathecae slender, oblong (
<figureCitation id="135E2A4CFF8BED5F2A56FEDBFE68FEEF" box="[345,464,352,378]" captionStart="FIGURES 84 – 87" captionStartId="27.[151,269,1929,1953]" captionTargetBox="[245,1343,774,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[245,1438,774,1901]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 84 – 87. Chrysopilus caligatus sp. n., male holotype: 84 — Wing, 85 — Antenna, 86 — Maxillary palpus, female paratype: 87 — Spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177250/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Figure 
<number id="3DAD24EEFF8BED5F2AA0FEDBFE68FEEF" box="[431,464,352,378]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="87.0">87</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37F6542FF8BED5F2BCAFE3CFC0FFE37" box="[197,951,391,418]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BDA36C9FF8BED5F2BCAFE3CFC0FFE37" blockId="29.[151,1437,152,498]" box="[197,951,391,418]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis id="B911EADBFF8BED5F2BCAFE3CFEDDFE34" bold="true" box="[197,357,391,417]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Distribution.</emphasis>
This species is known only from the type-locality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37F6542FF8BED5F2BCAFE14FD74FE67" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BDA36C9FF8BED5F2BCAFE14FD74FE67" blockId="29.[151,1437,152,498]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis id="B911EADBFF8BED5F2BCAFE14FEEAFE5C" bold="true" box="[197,338,431,457]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name comes from the Latin word 
<taxonomicName id="4C654D4AFF8BED5F287EFE0BFC65FE5C" box="[881,989,432,457]" class="Insecta" family="Rhagionidae" genus="Chrysopilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caligatus">
<emphasis id="B911EADBFF8BED5F287EFE0BFC65FE5C" box="[881,989,432,457]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">caligatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, common soldier, as a reference to the wing brown stripes, resembling a military dress.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
